      "content": "That makes sense for a formal setting, but I don't want it to feel too sanitized. Even if they're being \"coded,\" their underlying views should still feel heavy and pointed. For example, if one of the leaders is more of a hardliner, how would they express their concerns about the \"changing neighborhood\" without necessarily using a slur? Could you give me a few different variations of how they might express that tension? I want to see the spectrum of how they justify their views on keeping certain people in their 'place'.",
